The police in Bayelsa State have arrested two suspects with a truckload of mattresses allegedly meant for flood victims. The mattresses, it was learned, were warehoused in an undisclosed location in Yenagoa the state capital when the suspect’s break-in and stole the mattresses. Civil Liberties Organisation (CLO) in the state had raised alarm over the stolen mattresses which prompted the police to react. Confirming the incident, Spokesman of the command, Mr Asinim Bustwat said in a statement “Following a tip-off, Operatives of Bayelsa State Police Command have arrested one Shehu Yola ‘m’ 42 years and one Sunday Emmanuel ‘m’ 28 years, at Okaka, Yenagoa. “The suspects were arrested on 18 February 2021, at about 2100hours, with a truckload of mattresses suspected to be stolen property. “The Commissioner of Police CP Mike Okoli fsi, has ordered for discreet Investigation to unravel the source of the mattresses.”\ Vanguard News Nigeria The Police Command in Bayelsa says its officers have arrested two taxi drivers for allegedly raping a female dancer. April 2, 2018 In "News" The Bayelsa State police command yesterday paraded seven suspects among them two serving policemen involved in last month abduction of Mrs. Rosaline Eruani, mother of the state Commissioner for Health, Dr. Azipabu Eruani. However one of the suspects, who is also a policeman, is currently on the run after collecting… September 12, 2009 In "News" The Bayelsa Police Command has arrested a 20-year-old man for allegedly raping a 5-year-old girl to death in Akedei Community, a riverine suburb in Sagbama Local Government Area of Bayelsa. August 12, 2016 In "News"